Michael Brown Sr. has released a public service announcement shortly before the grand jury decision on whether or not to indict the police officer who shot dead his son, Michael Brown.

In it, he appeals for calm and non-violence among those who might protest, saying that 'hurting others is not the answer.'

He also takes a moment to thank many of the protesters for 'lifting [their] voices to end racial profiling and police intimidation.'

This as Darren Wilson, the officer responsible for the fatal shooting, has said he feels 'confident' he won't be charged by the grand jury and is working with city officials to negotiate his resignation from the Ferguson Police Department.

