Wilson claims he then drew his weapon but Brown tried to wrestle it from him while continuing to punch him in the face.

During that struggle for his gun, Wilson said he got off two shots, missing the Brown on the first and hitting him in the hand with the second.

When Brown tried to escape, Wilson allegedly stated that he continued to shoot, firing off the fatal volley of shots when Brown turned and started rushing towards him.

This account is in stark contrast with that of several eye witnesses, and Brown's companion Johnson, who have claimed that the unarmed teen had his hands up, or by his side, and begged the officer 'Stop shooting.'

The office of St Louis Prosecutor Bob McCulloch has said that they will unseal all evidence reviewed by the Grand Jury following their decision and release it to the public. 

 

 

 

